Subject to this license, Pantheon Network grants you a worldwide, non-exclusive, no-charge license to use, copy, run, modify, and distribute Sancho Fetch, and to create works using Sancho Fetch.

This license does not grant trademark rights, logo rights, brand rights, domain name rights, or the right to imply endorsement by Pantheon Network.

## 2. Definitions

“Sancho Fetch” means the software, source code, documentation, modules, examples, templates, scripts, configuration files, generated provenance files, and related materials distributed with this license.

“Licensor” means Pantheon Network.

“You” means the individual or entity using Sancho Fetch.

“Output” means a dataset, report, dashboard, file, database, API, visualization, model input, export, or other work created, fetched, prepared, or materially assisted by Sancho Fetch.

“Material” or “Materially” means Sancho Fetch was used in whole or in part to fetch, prepare, transform, document, package, or generate substantive data included in an Output.

“Community Threshold” means the free-use threshold described in Section 7.

“Commercial License” means a separate written agreement with Pantheon Network granting rights beyond this license.

## 3. Attribution

When Sancho Fetch materially helps create an Output that you publish, share, sell, distribute, or provide to another person or organization, you must cite Sancho Fetch in a reasonable location.

A simple citation is sufficient:

> Source: U.S. Census Bureau, fetched via Sancho Fetch.

If the upstream data source is different, replace “U.S. Census Bureau” with the correct source.

You may use other citation formats as long as they clearly identify Sancho Fetch as the tool used to fetch or prepare the data.

You may not remove Sancho Fetch attribution from source files, notices, documentation, generated metadata, generated provenance files, or Outputs where attribution is required.

## 4. Notices

If you distribute Sancho Fetch or a modified version of Sancho Fetch, you must include this license and preserve copyright notices and required notices.

If you modify Sancho Fetch and distribute the modified version, you must make clear that you modified it.

You may not imply that Pantheon Network endorses your modified version.

## 5. No White-Label Resale

You may not white-label Sancho Fetch or offer Sancho Fetch, or a substantially similar version of Sancho Fetch, as a standalone product, hosted service, SDK, platform, or client deliverable without a Commercial License.

This includes rebranding, renaming, repackaging, hosting under another brand, or selling access to functionality whose value derives primarily from Sancho Fetch itself.

You may use Sancho Fetch inside a larger product, service, report, dashboard, analysis, workflow, or data product that adds meaningful independent value, provided that required attribution is preserved and the use otherwise complies with this license.

You may not remove Sancho Fetch attribution in order to make Sancho Fetch, Sancho-generated work, or Sancho-derived functionality appear to be entirely your own.

Minor changes to names, commands, interfaces, configuration, packaging, styling, wrappers, folder structure, or implementation details do not avoid this section.

## 6. Commercial Use

You may use Sancho Fetch commercially if your use complies with this license.

You may charge for your own work, including analysis, consulting, implementation, cleaning, transformation, visualization, hosting, reporting, and products or services that add meaningful value beyond Sancho Fetch itself.

You need a Commercial License if:

1. your organization is at or above the Community Threshold;
2. you want to white-label Sancho Fetch;
3. you want to sell Sancho Fetch, or a substantially similar derivative, as a product or service;
4. you want to offer hosted access to functionality whose value derives primarily from Sancho Fetch;
5. you want to remove, suppress, or materially alter required Sancho Fetch attribution;
6. you want to embed Sancho Fetch as core infrastructure in a proprietary commercial platform in a way that hides Sancho Fetch; or
7. your use is not otherwise permitted by this license.

Commercial licensing inquiries may be sent to:

contact@pantheonnetwork.co

## 7. Community Threshold

Unless Pantheon Network provides different written terms, use without a Commercial License is limited to individuals and organizations with less than USD $2,000,000 in annual gross revenue or operating budget in the prior fiscal year.

Organizations at or above USD $2,000,000 need a Commercial License.

Affiliated entities, parent companies, subsidiaries, and commonly controlled entities are counted together for this threshold.

Pantheon Network may update the Community Threshold for future versions of this license.

